{
  "texts": [
    "In fact, the generation of hypotheses for research projects, especially data-driven hypotheses, most likely use divergent thinking with multiple possible correct answers, whereas the generation of hypotheses to solve a puzzle likely uses convergent thinking with a limited number of correct answers 19.",
    "Within scientific thinking, some researchers have also studied hypothesis generation.",
    "Thomas et al.",
    "44 proposed a human judgment framework to generate hypotheses and explained hypothesis testing and human judgment.",
    "Their study, however, was focused on human judgment, decision-making, and the hypotheses generated in order to do so."
  ]
}